						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the kitchen in the Tiruttaḷīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanachakravartin Śrīvallabhadēva Year 20.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record may be assigned to c. 12th Century on palaeographical grounds.</p>						

						<p>It states that the kitchen <hi rend="italic">(tirumaḍaippaḷḷi),</hi> on the wall of which the present inscription has been engraved was caused to be constructed in the temple of Tiruttaḷiyāṇḍār at Tirupputtūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Kēraḷaśiṅgavaḷanāḍu by the queen Ulagamuḻuduḍaiyār, who is called <hi rend="italic">muḍikkīḻnambirāṭṭiyār</hi> of the said king.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIV, No. 248.</p>						

						</summary>
